<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1014,2011]" pageId="7" pageNumber="371">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,580,1122,1147]" pageId="7" pageNumber="371">
External morphology (
<figureCitation box="[474,545,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1505,1527]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,214,1484]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,195,1484]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Desmacella annexa (MNRJ 2860) in SEM. A, preserved specimen; B, thick section showing the ectosome and choanosome; C, size variation of tylostyles; D, tylostyle base; E, size variation of toxiform microxeas; F, sigma I and sigma II; G, details of sigma I microspines; H, details of toxiform microxea microspines; I, details of sigma II microspines. Scale bars: A = 1 cm; B = 200 µm; C = 100 µm; D = 10 µm; E = 20 µm; F = 10 µm; G – H = 2 µm; I = 1 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239398/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="371">
Fig. 
<number box="[530,545,1122,1147]" pageId="7" pageNumber="371" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A).
</emphasis>
Fragments, thinly encrusting 
<number box="[925,939,1123,1147]" pageId="7" pageNumber="371" value="2.0">2</number>
<date box="[948,985,1123,1147]" pageId="7" pageNumber="371">
x 
<quantity box="[971,985,1123,1147]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="371" unit="cm" value="1.0">1</quantity>
</date>
cm (length x width). Oscules were not found, vaguely hispid surface, consistency is fragile and colour cream in ethanol.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1014,2011]" pageId="7" pageNumber="371">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,422,1194,1219]" pageId="7" pageNumber="371">
Skeleton (
<figureCitation box="[317,387,1194,1219]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1505,1527]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,214,1484]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,195,1484]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Desmacella annexa (MNRJ 2860) in SEM. A, preserved specimen; B, thick section showing the ectosome and choanosome; C, size variation of tylostyles; D, tylostyle base; E, size variation of toxiform microxeas; F, sigma I and sigma II; G, details of sigma I microspines; H, details of toxiform microxea microspines; I, details of sigma II microspines. Scale bars: A = 1 cm; B = 200 µm; C = 100 µm; D = 10 µm; E = 20 µm; F = 10 µm; G – H = 2 µm; I = 1 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239398/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="371">
Fig. 
<number box="[372,387,1194,1219]" pageId="7" pageNumber="371" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
B).
</emphasis>
There is no special ectosomal skeleton. Choanosomal skeleton formed by large tylostyles making massive plumose bundles; well developed spongin fibres. Abundant sigmas (I and II) appear to be randomly distributed. Toxiform microxeas were not recognized.
</paragraph>
